  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "TEG1Olwn1r5m/33FKYHppbvEZGc=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:32.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# document model vs document editor vs app serves different purposes\n\nThree distinct document types serve different needs:\n\n| Type | Purpose | Document Type |\n|------|---------|---------------|\n| **Document Model** | Defines structure \u2014 schema and operations for a document type | `powerhouse/document-model` |\n| **Document Editor** | UI for editing a single document instance | `powerhouse/document-editor` |\n| **App (Drive Editor)** | UI for managing collections of documents in a drive | `powerhouse/app` |\n\nThe critical distinction: when a user says \"create an app\" or \"manage multiple documents,\" create a `powerhouse/app`, NOT a `powerhouse/document-model`.\n\nSince [[apps use useSelectedDrive to access drive state and filter nodes]], apps work at the drive level. Since [[editors use the modern React hooks pattern from reactor-browser]], editors work at the individual document level.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[architecture decisions]]",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:32.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:32.000Z"
    }
  },
